            "answer_text": "Lets assume that the Cost Price(CP) for the article is =100 \u2234Marked Price(MP) = CP+30% of CP= 100+((30/100)*100)=130 Since Discount(D) is applied on the MP, Selling Price(SP) = MP-(D% * MP) \u2234SP = 130 - ((30/100)*130)= 130 - 39= 91 Since SP is lower than CP, Loss(L) = CP-SP = 100 -91=9 \u2234L% = (L/CP)*100= (9/100)*100=9% Answer Loss% is 9% PS- If you have any doubt regarding to the above solving please feel free to ask in the comment section PSS- If you feel that x% increase then x% decrease cancel each other out, this question proves that they don\u2019t. So don\u2019t make a mistake! :) ",
